Class MathVariable

  • java.lang.Object
    • Argument
      • Variable
        • MathVariable
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.util.Comparator

    public class MathVariable
extends Variable
    This class defines a math variable in Prolog syntax. Its name (by convention) must begin with a capitol letter; that convention is NOT enforced. This sub-class of Variable is for arguments that will be bound to numbers, booleans, strings, or Individuals. In Example-Generation, constraints on the value of this variable are stored in its fields.

    Serialized Form
